Package: fono
Architecture: linux-any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, libxkbcommon-x11-0
Recommends: pipewire | pulseaudio, wtype | ydotool | xdotool
Description: Talk to your computer, a local voice-AI stack in one binary
 Fono gives your computer a voice interface: press a key and speak, and it
 types, answers, or acts. It's the entire voice-AI stack (speech-to-text,
 natural voices, a local LLM, wake word, speaker ID) in one small binary,
 local by default, cloud only when you opt in. No Electron, no WebKit, no
 Python runtime.
